      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "perf(queue): raise exact-review target ramp",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nOpenClaw's exact-review backlog is no longer draining at the 8-target-slot cap: live samples moved from 176 to 179 pending while all 8 OpenClaw slots were leased.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nRaise exact-review admission from 12 to 14 global slots and the per-target cap from 8 to 10. This gives OpenClaw two more active exact-review workers while preserving four global slots for other target repositories.\n\nThis also makes the automation-limits drift checker accept oxfmt-aligned markdown tables, which avoids a false drift failure after formatting `docs/limits.md`.\n\n## User Impact\n\nClawSweeper should drain the OpenClaw review backlog faster without letting one target repository consume the entire exact-review pool.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `node --test test/dashboard-worker.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/check-limits.ts`\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check dashboard/worker.ts dashboard/wrangler.toml scripts/check-limits.ts test/dashboard-worker.test.ts README.md docs/limits.md docs/live-dashboard.md docs/target-dispatcher.md config/automation-limits.json && git diff --check`\n- autoreview clean: no accepted/actionable findings reported\n",
